            <fr:title text="Constructible sets compute Booleanisation">Constructible sets compute Booleanisation</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  For a distributive lattice <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>, the poset of constructible subsets of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex> is isomorphic to the Booleanisation of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>, i.e. the free Boolean algebra associated to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>. In particular, the <fr:link href="/topl-F1KS/" title="Constructible topology" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-F1KS/" display-uri="topl-F1KS" type="local">constructible topology</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex> is the Priestley topology.
</html:p>
 
   
